	<h3>Web Application for Reporting Vandalism of Trees</h3>
	<h4>Course: </span>CPSC 310 - Software Engineering</h4>
	<h4>Skills acquired: </span>Java, GWT, XML, Google App Engine</h4>
	<p>My team and I designed and developed a web application that allowed users to report vandalism and share their interests in trees with other tree lovers. We imported and parsed large datasets about individual trees located in the lower mainland. After parsing and storing the data, we then created a search function to allow users to look for trees that they liked, and even plot a route between multiple trees so they can set up tours. We also created a commenting and reporting system to allow users to leave comments about the trees they liked. If they found a tree that was vandalized, they can report it as well and an administrator would be able to dispatch a government worker to take a look. To further enhance the social capabilities of our app, we implemented Facebook sharing functionality where you can share your favourite trees to your friends. During this software development process, we followed the Agile methodology, from creating user stories, to holding scrums, to doing sprint planning and user story estimation.</p>
